benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/export/{accountId} - Export account data

covered: Valid Request: Successful exports with required-only and with optional headers; 200 with application/octet-stream body.
Header Validation: Missing required X-Killbill-CreatedBy returns 400; extra and legacy headers are tolerated without failing the request.
Path Parameter Validation: Malformed UUID and injection attempts return 400.
Not Found Handling: 404 for non-existent account and when DB is empty.
Authorization: 401 for unauthenticated access (if authentication is required).
Error Handling: 500 when export service is unavailable; 504 on long-running operation timeout; 405 for unsupported method.
Performance/Resilience: Large export size, slow downstream within timeout, and concurrent GET requests validated.
Regression: Ensures Content-Type application/octet-stream is present on success.
N/A Items: Query parameters and pagination are not applicable for this endpoint.
gaps: Rate Limiting: No scenarios for throttling/429 responses or Retry-After headers under burst traffic.
Caching Behavior: No verification of ETag/Last-Modified/Cache-Control headers or 304 Not Modified behavior.
Authorization (Forbidden): No 403 case for authenticated but unauthorized user/tenant.
Empty Response Semantics: No explicit test for exporting an existing account with no data (clarify whether to return minimal archive vs 204/empty body).
Binary Integrity: No assertion that the octet-stream is a valid, parseable archive (e.g., ZIP/TAR) with expected contents.
Content-Disposition: No test for presence/format of download filename header, if applicable.
Observability: No validation of traceability headers (e.g., X-Request-Id/Correlation-Id) to aid troubleshooting.
recommendations: Add rate limiting tests: send bursts exceeding expected thresholds, assert 429 with Retry-After; verify any rate-limit headers if implemented.
Add caching scenarios: verify ETag/Last-Modified and subsequent conditional requests (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since) yielding 304 or refreshed content.
Add a 403 scenario: authenticated user lacking permission/scope should receive 403.
Add a scenario for exporting an account with no associated data; assert documented behavior (status code and minimal archive presence/size).
Validate archive integrity by opening the returned octet-stream as a ZIP/TAR and verifying it is parseable and contains expected structures.
Verify presence and format of Content-Disposition filename (e.g., accountId-export.zip) if part of the API contract, or document that it is intentionally omitted.
Optionally test Accept header behavior (e.g., request non-supported types leading to 406) if content negotiation is part of the API.
